Best one I've found, with just a few annoyances: 1. The flashing lights take *far* too much screen space, which leaves hardly any space for the setlist! The lights can be literally 1/4 of the height and it would be fine. 2. The navigation in general is bonkers - like really unhinged in places! I defy anyone to work out how to edit a song without getting utterly confused. 3. In "gig" mode, the fact that you can accidentally edit your set list (including the BPMs!) is completely inexcusable when there is a "rehearsal" mode as well. Playing live? Write out a set list with the track BPMs on it as a back up, because this app will one day f* you up on stage. So in summary: a usability-free zone, but But APART from that, comparatively good.
Terribly inaccurate tap tempo. When triggering it there's always a delay before it starts, making timing very difficult. Total garage in my opinion.

content: Very important features are needed: Auto-sync song list to user's Google account, sort songs to name or date...

content: Needs a way to import csv or copy previous setlist to edit. When are going to get the upgrades? Flashing, import setlist etc..

Updates over the past few years have lost "full-screen flash," which I need for silent metronome during live performance. Used to LOVE this app.. can't use it anymore. I'm a professional pianist, make my living accompanying. I used this app happily for years until it's best creatures started disappearing. The lost "full-screen flash" was even in dark mode.. used to be wonderful. Recent updates have also lost the capability of quickly toggling between sound vs mute by tapping the beat links.
replyContent: Hi, we have never added the full screen flash to the Android version of this app. We will add it soon.

content: Tempo continues to try and reinvent the wheel. I will no longer recommend this app to my students. Why on Earth would you take the accent markings away??
replyContent: We spend significant effort in implementing new features. We are sorry if you prefer developers that don't update their apps. The accent markings are right there. You can tap on the LEDs to change the accent state.

However, updates have changed my opinion since the beginning of my experience with this app from 1 star to 4 stars because they have remedied the copy issue making it a fantastic app to copy from a master list into various set lists. I am not sure on the deletion of song lists - just back up or "share" them to an email and you can restore within seconds. I give 4 stars instead of 5 because, although there have been strides to fix the issues, there are a few features I would like to see added such as a sort feature (A-Z). This would be extremely helpful with a "master" list. Other than that, I have made almost a 180 in my attitude and my endorsement for this app. I highly reccommend it now. I tried several free apps, all of which were a bust. This one is versatile and lightweight; and I've only used the most basic of features. Great for drum practice, but should work well with many other applications. Oh, and I'm even on an older model phone.
Love it
Great app! (4 out of 5 because it crashes quite often on Samsung S5)

I love this app, it has a great layout, and is easy to use, but it freezes up my phone at least once every time I use it (where I have to restart my phone to un-freeze it) . Today it froze twice, and the second time the screen went entirely black and my phone was unresponsive, so I had to actually take out the battery to even restart it. The tap to set tempo feature also doesn't always work. I really wanted to give this five stars, but I can't with the bugs it has right now, please fix these. Thanks!
Pales in comparison with the iPhone version. Too simplistic and inaccurate! Limited number of time signatures and subdivision accents. Only benefit is ability to save setlists.
This is definitely the best metronome on Android. I'm looking forward to an update that adds a full flashing screen however, similar to the iOS version.

Great Visual App. I prefer the dark theme. Best for stage viewing for me. Had copy and select issues. Did a reinstall and runs much better. But the reinstall seems stable.
Absolutely fantastic.  I would highly recommend this to amyone.
I loveeee this app but it's been acting up lately..Deleting all of my saved set list that I use ...which is about 100+ songs' BPM......FIX THISSSSSS !!!!

Galaxy S3 & HTC inspire- I'm using the app for my church set lists. It's simple to create set lists and add/overwrite the songs. However we kept noticing the click would start lagging and slow down then it would rubber band bank up to speed. It would do it just enough to throw everyone off. I have airplane mode on, so it's not notifications. I'll continue to use the app to see if it's just an anomaly. I'll update my rating when I see the problem is fixed.

This ap is really great. But, my bandmate has an iPhone and the version for ios has more features that are nice, like a sound set that counts. Would give 5 stars if the android version had more of the bells and wistles.
Does everything I need.

I had this app on ios and had zero problems. Ran smooth 100% of the time on stage and off and have recommended it to alot of people. Recently upgraded to the galaxy s5 and at band practice today while going through the set list on the app it froze my phone twice! Luckily it was practice and not a show... very dissapointed in this app for the s5.. also the app doesnt have as many features as the ios version.. I mean its a brand new phone and this app froze it twice in 20 mins.. this sucks please fix!!!
So far...so good...

This app would be perfect if it would allow me to copy songs properly from one setlist to another.   I can copy songs 1-10 no problem,  but then trying to select any song past #10 actually selects songs from 1-10 all over again.  I'm prepping for a gig right now and this is brutal. I can't even edit the setlist on my computer without diving into hundreds of lines of code.
Buggy

Some things I would love to have, call then feature requests An easy way to edit the XML file on a computer. Event driven notifications e.g. don't forget the bridge! Notification comes up at bar 48 and closes 4 bars later. Strobe effect, control phone led/ screen brightness in time with the click.
5 stars, best metronome app I could find!
App keeps freezing if you try to change time signatures. I had to restart my phone 4 times to get through a set list!!!
Can only scroll down. Scroll up button doesn't work. Only scrolling down. Also is it possible to change the pattern on existing songs? (without having to add a new song)

Works fine as a standard metronome, but lacks most of the impressive features that the iPhone version had... Wouldn't have bought it for my android if I'd know it lacked so much.  Mainly I miss the different view modes, and especially on with big next/previous buttons to cycle through your set list.  Also, proximity trigger features.  I'd love this if it became more like the iOS version!
Very useful.
Fantastic, functional and fuss-free.
Since the update I cannot adjust the volume.
Been using this for years now and it does the job well.
Definitely my fave android metronome. After recent update, however, I can no longer use my hardware volume buttons while the app is running. Sony Xperia Z, Kit Kat
Great job. So glad its on android. First used it on my iPad.
By far the best metronome on Android due to its user-friendly interface and seemingly unlimited possibilities. Also helps that it's the least annoying click available!

At first I thought there's something wrong with my backing track but tested this with the iPad version and this one begins to lag behind after a few bars. I'm running this with Samsung Note 8.0. Devs please fix. I use this on my live rig.

Excellent app, well worth the money. However I wish that the Android version came with a tuner.
I love this app, any musician should definitely use It.

Before buying, I read some of the other reviews that were negative. It made me a bit apprehensive but it is easy to use and I've had no problems. Smart intuitive design.  Does  one song after another- just hit down arrow. Easy to edit . Droid version 2.0.2
Um i t worked but now my set list wont work and it shuts down immediately
replyContent: There is a bug that prevents setlists with the character "&" from working. Please open your setlist file in a text editor to remove all occurrences of that character, or contact us at tempo android@frozenape.com for help.

content: We use this for a "click" for our church band.
Best trainer to now  the beats
This App is very user friendly and precise.......Highly recommend!

I definitely like the customizable accent patterns; as a drummer, this is really useful. However, I wish there were odd compound meters (5/8, 7/8, etc.) or a higher max tempo. The iOS version goes up to 800, this one only goes up to 400.

I have this same app in my iPod and in my Droid phone.  The options for the app in Droid are minimal in comparison to the exact same app in my iPod (I've paid for both). Also, the one for Droid has a delay after hitting play, which makes it hard to restart in sync with a current rhythm while playing live. I LOVE this app and give it 5 stars but only for the Mac's App Store version... as far as the Droid one, I keep waiting for Frozen Ape to make it as good as the Mac... so only 2 stars here.

It crashed continually on my 2 Android devices once I'd spent hours inputting setlists, bpms, tempos, etc. Also, transferring the data file from one device to the other as a backup, and to be able to use both devices, failed miserably - Tempo failed to recognise the file, lost its existing data but didn't pick up the new data.A waste of time as anything other than a simple metronome.

I loved this app for the iphone but this version is lacking a lot of features that I used quite a bit. i.e. this version has the "power save mode" always enabled so when I press the play button the tempo starts about half a beat behind rather than as soon as a push it, which is probably the most important aspect of this app to me. Also I liked the feature of being able to switch between "Basic, Preset, Setlist, Practice, and Gig" modes. Also there's no panning option, or fullscreen flash, you get the gist.
5 stars if you support arbitrary time signatures and subdivisions, not just a fixed list of presets. But still the best metronome app out there!
Hi I'm just wondering when there will be a voice count addition to the metronome. I know the iPhone version has it but the Android doesn't seem to. Thanks.
Best metronome I have used

Very disappointed with this app after purchase. Had the iOS version for years and was sad to see that the android version, unlike the iOS version, lacks a tuner and the ability to remove the giant set list box out of view.  Incredibly bare bones metronome. Will be looking for another one.
Works great just would like some of the iPhone features and for the stop and start button to launch exactly when you hit it

Obviously, this is a great app; intuitive and efficient. Sound sets are great. Please add subdivisions such as quintuplets, septuplets, or even nonuplets to make the app better. Being able to add a preset such as time signature and tempo changes would also be a bonus.
Would be exponentially better if there was a bulk song list available to store and pull song by song, rather than program each song each set.
Nuff said!!!

20/12/2013: Still can't move songs between lists. Some tempos not compatible with ios version if copying file from other device. Android version of this app is only used as backup shld not have iPad, not the same professional standard & not recommend for multiple sets.

I love this app. So amazing with different sigs and everything. Please keep this current look, I absolutely love it. Thanks developers. Also thanks for potrait mode, love you guys

I love this metronome app.  I used it on my Iphone and now have switched to a Nexus 5.    They are quickly adding features to make it match the Iphone version.  The interface is clean and intuitive.   I tried 3 other metronome apps and hated them.   This is my favorite by far.  The developer is also very responsive.  I wanted portrait mode and emailed him and he gets right back to me.   Now we have portrait mode.   This app will keep getting better!
Best metronome app out!!
Works great for our worship team. Only wished you could synchronize devices for multiple users.

I'm working with tempo metronome almost 2years on iphone4 and iphone 3gs (ios5 and ios7) with all bands and live concerts where I play but I must say that on android Jelly-Bean the Tempo is in pure quality!!! 1) It works only in one landscape mode (one side) 2) No profile option (gig,practice,setlist) hard to switch next song in gig. 3) The play button does not start imediately (a second or half latency) 4) And the click sound is not the same all time: for example on 4/4 beat with out accents added it sounds like on 2nd beat the click sound is lower and 1,3,4 is louder. Sounds not smooth.  5)  imported setlists takes about 6minutes to open app every time!!!  Im professional session drummer and I have sbout 20setlist by now and it is good to have all tempos and setlists in my pocket but on android its cofusing!  And ofcourse no search song option at all! :(  3stars only for that its ONLY app that offers to save setlists and create own setlists. Let me know is there any other app!
Doesn't run as smoothly as on iOS. It's also locked into the landscape orientation, which is absurd and the biggest reason why I refunded it.
Great app

I know that android apps are usually behind the apple ios apps, but this one is seriously behind. Can we get an update to have this app be somewhat close to what the ios has. This version of the app is basically just a trial. It shoudve been a free app.

Great job

Love it. Absolutely worth the money!

Went from best to worst! I had it on my iphone and it was awesome but, when I switched to a gallaxy it was nit the same. Tap is useless, it does not start in time, jumps beats and worst if all, it plays the wrong tempo from the play list. A real drag when playing live and you punch up a song and the tempo is wrong. Please fix this so I can be happy again!

There may be some bugs in the details of this metronome, but it is apparent that this metronome was made by musicians.

I am amazed that the hasn't been a serious update ever. Where is the 7/8 time? Poor developing

I just switched from the 4s to the s4.  This sucks on the s4...too much lag time when pushing the play button.  Too hard to edit.  Make it the same as the iphone version and I'll be a very happy camper.  Thank you

Loved Tempo on my old iPod but the Android port is clumsy and doesn't have the full set of features that I used on the iPod. I am disappointed and as there have been no  upgrades I am looking for another metronome.
replyContent: We just released an update. Please understand that the iOS version has been in development for years, and it takes time to introduce all its features to Android.

content: Works well, but doesn't function in portrait mode, nor can you delete song names.   Add in different themes? I like blue from iOS. Please bring both platforms into equal standing!

Not nearly as good as it is on the iPad. Doesn't fit the display quite right, the ability to change from quarters to eights, use of screen space not as good. It will get there if they address these concerns but it is not there yet.

I came from Ipod & really wanted this on my tablet for the reference tone keyboard for practicing vocals on the go.  In the other version, it's in the Settings options & this one lacks this, and some other settings.
For what this is, I am personally fully satisfied with what it has to offer and its capabilities.  As basic as this is, it does give me the help that I need.

I had this app on my iPhone and loved it. For whatever reason, the Android version is less intuitive and more limiting.  I really wish they would make the 2 apps exactly the same. I miss the iPhone Version!
What would make this app 100% perfect it the ability to drag and drop saved songs to our church setlist.

I agree with everybody the app is amazing, but every Sunday I have to set the list and order. Could you guys please work on SAVE the tempo of the music then on Sundays all we need to do is load that song or tempo and re-order. This will be be great so that way we use the same tempo everytime. Please work on that ASAP  I already sent an email asking you guys but never got any response

I agree with all the others. This app is a really amazing app. We use it for our church worship sets as well. Its very easy to use, has a great UI and more....but...we really need the set list re-order asap. We will often change a set the day before and having to redo an entire setlist is a real pain. Other then that, again, it's really awesome.
Please add Tempo 2 like iPhone. Need to be able to drag songs between setlists.
Its great but i wish it had a voice selection for the clicks 1234, 1e&a, 1&a. And  individual Accent click sounds you can interchange

I currently have this  app on my iPhone and figured I'd rather have it on my Nexus 7. This version looks like crap on the Nexus 7 and is missing a lot if features available on the iOS version. You can't reorder set lists. You can tell it to just play for X number of measures like you can on the iOS version. Overall sure there is something better out there for a Android Metronome.
looks like bugs and lock-ups have been fixed. Had to wait months and reinstal.I willcontinue in test mode ubtil I trust it for a performance. ipad version is proven....will update! Galaxy III.
After using the iOS version, this one is definitely lacking, especially the ability to pan left and right which is pretty essential.
the primary disappointment is that the continuously moving pendulum (below the beat counter on the iphone version) is totally missing from the android version.
Even beats my physical korg one! Almost too many options....

I wish the subdivision was like a Boss DB-90, to where there are different pitches for the different subdivisions, like exactly lol. I also wish we could have complete control over the subdivision, like the sliders on a doctor beat.
its a shame

I came from Iphone and the android version really needs the drag and drop functionality with the set lists.  Also, it seems it takes a split second for the tempo to start which makes it hard to stop and start the tempo right on time while you're in the middle of playing a song. This isn't an issue on the Iphone. I guess it's an android issue because other metronome apps don't start right on time either.
Where is the set list feature for android? Don't buy this app until they provide it, that's my opinion.  I feel misled and ripped off.

Tempo is the best mentronome app, without competition. On iPhone it's absolutely perfect, but the Android version lacks an absolutely critical feature: Re-ordering of songs in the setlists. A drag/drop feature would solve this, but now setlists has to be completely redone if you wish to change the order of the songs. Frozen Ape should REALLY consider adding this feature.

This was my most used app on my iPhone but now I have android and this app needs updating. The main thing for me is that you can't smoothly adjust the tempo on the fly. Say you are playing a gig and the band say that you are playing too slow, you press the + button but then the click starts again out of time meaning you'd either have a completely out of time click or have to turn it off. The iPhone version doesn't do this, it just increases the speed of the current click meaning no-one notices the subtle increase. This is probably still the best app on android but please Frozen ape make it better or ideally as good as the iPhone version - that would be awesome!

The iOS version, while 'best selling' is lacking in a number of areas... This version (that I've been awaiting for years! ) is buggy, lacks features and is a shadow of the iPhone version. I guess perhaps updates will come?!

By far the best app for using in a live setting. We use it for our church worship sets and im soooo glad its out for android phones now!! We have been using this app using an ipod or ipad (depending on whos scheduled) but now if not available we can use my phone! Only one thing keeping this from being 5 stars... the inability to drag n drop songs and create separate set-lists as easily as on the apple products.  :( PLEASE PLEASE upgrade soon!!!!

Bought this app a month ago and it was working fine. Last night the app just froze and my screen went dark. Wtf? Anybody else have this problem? I've uninstalled and reinstalled but problem still persists.
I play three shows a week with this app. Completely replaced my click station.
Bring the advanced version to android.  I love this app but need to be able to organize the set lists on the fly. I'm talking about drag n drop.
This app is cool and easy to use but I really want the tempo advance app. Please frozen ape, make advance for Android. Thank you
